urss -- micro RSS generator
===========================

- fully POSIX c99
- compiled config
- RSS 0.92[0]
- UNIX pipes only

usage
-----
urss takes input and produces output through UNIX pipes;
e.g. `cat index.html post1.html ... | urss > index.rss`

urss looks for:
- item: all of the following must be within `ITEM_TAG`
- title: any string within `TITLE_TAG` 
- link: any string within `LINK_TAG`
- description: any string within `DESC_TAG`

e.g.
Given the following HTML snippet:
```html
<article>
  <h1>My Title</h1>
  <link><a href=www.example.com>backlink to this article</a></link>
  <p>my really cool content</p>
</article>
```
with the following config:
```
ITEM_TAG = article
TITLE_TAG = h1
LINK_TAG = link
DESC_TAG = p
```

urss would produce the following XML snippet:
```
<item>
<title>My Title</title>
<link><a href=www.example.com>backlink to this article</a></link>
<description><p>my really cool content</p></description>
</item>
```

patching
--------
1. read the source

adding non-essential fields is trivial;
- add the relevant pairing of XML <-> HTML to `TYPES` and the type enumerator
- call `export_content` with the relevant field in the main loop 

please submit patches on either bug tracker[1][2], or to <git [at] notu [dot] dev> with the Subject: 'URSS PATCH: ...'.

